class Solution {
    public int findChampion(int n, int[][] edges) {
        int[] degree = new int[n];
        for (int[] e : edges) {
            degree[e[1]]++;
        }
        int champion = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (degree[i] == 0) {
                if (champion == -1) {
                    champion = i;
                } else {
                    return -1;
                }
            }
        }
        return champion;
    }
}
```
The first loop initializes the degree array by counting the number of incoming edges for each vertex. The second loop finds the champion: if there is a vertex with 0 incoming edges, the champion is this vertex. If there is more than one vertex with 0 incoming edges, the champion cannot be determined, so the code returns -1.

